{"session_id": 61, "bill_id": 21472, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1180, "bill_title": "repeal certain provisions found to be unconstitutional, which required insurers to obtain a countersignature on policies.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 3634, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3676, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3571, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3590, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3591, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3595, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3602, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3629, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3639, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3643, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3644, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 3651, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Insurance"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2007-01-31T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/hco16.mp3", "start_seconds": 2132.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-01-31T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/hco16.mp3", "start_seconds": 2132.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-01-31T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/hco16.mp3", "start_seconds": 2132.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-01-31T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/hco16.mp3", "start_seconds": 2132.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-02-15T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/sco27.mp3", "start_seconds": 1044.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-02-15T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/sco27.mp3", "start_seconds": 1044.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-02-15T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/sco27.mp3", "start_seconds": 1044.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2007-02-15T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SCO", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2007/sco27.mp3", "start_seconds": 1044.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 21472, "bill_version_id": 110741, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2007-01-25T08:47:35-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to repeal certain provisions found to be unconstitutional, which required insurers to obtain a countersignature on policies. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 58-6-62 be repealed. 58-6-62. No authorized insurer may make, write, issue, or place any policy, bond, contract of insurance, or general or floating policy upon persons or property, or covering a subject of insurance or bonding to be performed in South Dakota, unless the policy is written through a licensed resident insurance producer, or a licensed nonresident insurance producer, except where the license of the nonresident insurance producer is not required pursuant to subdivision \u00a7 58- 30-144(6), if countersigned by a resident insurance producer. If two or more insurers issue a single policy, it may be countersigned on behalf of all of them by one of the insurer's licensed resident insurance producers in this state. Any violation of this section is a Class 2 misdemeanor. Section 2. That \u00a7 58-6-63 be repealed. 58-6-63. The licensed resident insurance producer, if countersigning for a licensed nonresident insurance producer, shall receive for this service five percent of the total premium or twenty-five percent of the commission whichever is less. Either the resident insurance producer or the insurer, or both, shall enter this payment amount on the insurance producer's or insurer's record so that the state will receive the necessary tax required by law. The resident insurance producer has the option of waiving countersignature fees of less than two dollars. Section 3. That \u00a7 58-6-64 be repealed. 58-6-64. Any insurer requesting countersignature from a resident insurance producer shall furnish, for that insurance producer's permanent records, full information regarding policy number, name of insured, amount of premium applicable to South Dakota, and the name and license number of the licensed South Dakota nonresident insurance producer. On audit type policies, the company shall furnish full information at the audit period to the resident insurance producer regarding the earned premium applicable to the State of South Dakota. The insurer is obligated to see that the correct resident insurance producer countersignature fee is paid."}, {"bill_id": 21472, "bill_version_id": 112530, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2007-02-21T08:52:45-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 21472, "action_date": "2007-01-25T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 110857, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/110857.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 198, "committee_id_action": 923, "committee_id_assigned": 911, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 21472, "action_date": "2007-01-31T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 111267, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/111267.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 911, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 21472, "action_date": "2007-01-31T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 111267, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/111267.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 279, "committee_id_action": 911, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 66550, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [3572, 3576, 3588, 3619, 3642, 3644, 3645, 3650, 3663, 3676, 3658], "Excused": [3592, 3622]}}, {"bill_id": 21472, "action_date": "2007-01-31T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 111267, "document_url": "https: